# How It Works Section Redesign Spec

## Decision: Option B — Animated Node Diagram

**Rejected Option A (demo video)** for these reasons:
- Zero human employees means no one to record, edit, or update the video when UI changes
- Video files are 5–20MB+ — heavyweight for a homepage (especially mobile)
- Video accessibility (captions) adds maintenance surface
- Videos go stale; diagram is data-driven and can be updated in code

**Chosen Option B (animated node diagram)** because:
- Pure SVG/CSS — no external files, no CDN dependencies
- Scales to any screen size
- Updates automatically when framework names change
- Feels premium and technical — appropriate for a "personality intelligence platform"

## Diagram Structure

```
[Input box: 120 Questions]
      |
      v (animated pulse down arrow)
[Algorithm node: circular, glowing]
      |
  ----+--------+----------+----------
  |            |          |          |
[Strengths] [16 Types] [DISC]  [Enneagram]
  (amber)   (purple)   (pink)   (green)
```

## SVG Layout Spec

- Viewbox: `0 0 600 320` (responsive via `width: 100%; max-width: 600px`)
- Input box: rect, rounded 12px, navy border, centered top
- Arrow: animated `stroke-dashoffset` flowing downward
- Algorithm node: circle r=40, purple bg, pulsing glow ring
- Output nodes: 4 rounded-rect cards, positioned in row, each in framework color
- Connecting lines: SVG `<path>` with `stroke-dashoffset` animation, staggered 0.3s apart

## CSS Animations

```css
/* Flowing arrow — the signal moving from input to algorithm */
.flow-arrow {
  stroke-dasharray: 200;
  stroke-dashoffset: 200;
  animation: flow 2s ease-in-out infinite;
}
@keyframes flow {
  0%   { stroke-dashoffset: 200; opacity: 0.3; }
  50%  { stroke-dashoffset: 0;   opacity: 1;   }
  100% { stroke-dashoffset: -200; opacity: 0.3; }
}

/* Algorithm node glow */
.algo-node {
  animation: node-pulse 2.5s ease-in-out infinite;
}
@keyframes node-pulse {
  0%, 100% { filter: drop-shadow(0 0 6px rgba(124, 58, 237, 0.5)); }
  50%       { filter: drop-shadow(0 0 20px rgba(124, 58, 237, 0.9)); }
}

/* Output lines — staggered reveal */
.output-line:nth-child(1) { animation: line-in 0.6s 0.0s forwards; }
.output-line:nth-child(2) { animation: line-in 0.6s 0.2s forwards; }
.output-line:nth-child(3) { animation: line-in 0.6s 0.4s forwards; }
.output-line:nth-child(4) { animation: line-in 0.6s 0.6s forwards; }
@keyframes line-in {
  from { stroke-dashoffset: 150; }
  to   { stroke-dashoffset: 0;   }
}
```

## Reduced-Motion Variant

```css
@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  .flow-arrow, .algo-node, .output-line { animation: none; }
  /* Show static completed-state diagram */
  .flow-arrow { stroke-dashoffset: 0; opacity: 1; }
  .output-line { stroke-dashoffset: 0; }
}
```

## Section Copy (above diagram)

```
H2: "One test. Four frameworks. Your complete picture."
Subtext: "120 questions analyzed simultaneously across Strengths, 16 Types, DISC, and Enneagram."
```

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] Animated SVG node diagram replaces 3-step scroll-text layout
- [ ] Diagram shows: Input → Algorithm → 4 outputs (each in framework color)
- [ ] Flow animation uses only CSS — no GSAP for this element
- [ ] Static/completed state shown when prefers-reduced-motion
- [ ] Responsive: diagram fills container, readable on 375px mobile
- [ ] Zero layout shift when diagram loads (fixed viewBox, not dynamic)
